2. Differentiate between JRE, JVM and JDK.

Answer:

        JRE(Java Runtime Environment): This is a platform where Java programs are run.
                                       It could be different for different OS.
        JVM(Java Virtual Machine): This is used to convert the java byte-code into OS machine code.
        JDK(Java Development Kit): Java compiler comes with JDK.
                                   JDK is used to develop and execute Java applications.